# Error Handling Rules

## GraphQL Fetchers
- try/catch with typed `WordPressFetchError`
- Retry once on timeout/5xx only
- Return `null` for missing content → page calls `notFound()`

## Error Boundaries
- `error.tsx` on every route segment fetching WordPress data
- Client component with `reset()` retry
- User-friendly messages only — no stack traces

## Logging
```typescript
console.error('[CWMC]', { context, query, message });
```
Never log secrets, GraphQL URLs with auth, or form PII.

## Degraded Mode
- Static fallback contact info on error pages
- Serve stale ISR cache when available
